{"questionId":"14588617","questionHtml":"<p>On the following axes, sketch the graph of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo></math></p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/add619f40e17a78c5f7d7172cfeffa55f677608c.png\"></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/32520ad4131bb7a42becd914d3d0e753d88ea5bb.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>A1A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>Note</strong>: Award marks as follows:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><em><strong>A1</strong></em> for approximately correct roots, in the intervals&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><em><strong>A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-intercept AND local minimum in approximately correct positions.&nbsp;Allow for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-intercept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>, and for local minimum&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><em><strong>A1</strong></em> for approximately correct endpoints, with the left end in the intervals&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp;and the right end in the intervals&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14588617","referenceCode":"23N.2.SL.TZ2.3a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"On the following axes, sketch the graph of f for -4≤x≤3.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.3—Graphing"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}